We attribute the beneficial charge robustness of the silicon vacancy to its favourable environment. The available charge traps, namely carbon vacancy, in its vicinity support the VSi to be most of the time in the correct charge state. Investigations of the probability of ionisation of the carbon vacancy (see Fig. S7) reveal the defect to be a donor-like neighbour under photo illumination, further exclude \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
